list.t:
When a CGN is unable to create a mapping due to resource constraints
        or administrative restrictions (i.e., quotas):

          it MUST drop the original packet;
          it SHOULD send an ICMP Destination Unreachable message with code 1
            (Host Unreachable) to the sender;
          it SHOULD send a notification (e.g., SNMP trap) towards a
            management system (if configured to do so);
          and it MUST NOT delete existing mappings in order to "make room"
            for the new one. (This only applies to normal CGN behavior, not to
            manual operator intervention.)
